## Custom Energy Commissioning App Specification

### Overview

This application streamlines the commissioning process for custom energy commissioning jobs. It enables engineers to catalog assets, perform tests, upload certifications and images, and generate documents such as SWI, risk assessments & test results. Data is stored and presented via customer portal and professional documents.

### Context

Below is the context of the current situation:

New Development (**Aldi**) is building a new site and requires an electrical supply. They have employed a utility infrastructure provider, **Power On**, to install the substations, switches, transformers, and related equipment. Power On retains ownership of these assets until the station goes live.

Before a site can go live, it must be signed off by a commissioning agent, **Custom Energy**. When the commissioning agent visits the site, they will ideally begin by performing a risk assessment and completing the associated document (see attached).

Next, they proceed with the commissioning process, which involves:

- Identifying all assets and their details (e.g., serial numbers) and recording them in a spreadsheet.
- Performing a comprehensive series of tests on these assets, documenting the results and marking each as pass or fail.

Once all tests are complete and satisfactory, the commissioning agent can sign off the **SWI**. Once the system goes live the utility provider (**GTC**) adopts the substation.

### Objectives

\- Automate asset cataloging and testing workflows  
\- Generate SWI, risk assessment and testing documents  
\- Provide secure customer portal for document and historical access

### Actors

- Engineer
- Admin
- Customer Portal User

### Functional Requirements

- \- Asset cataloging with serial numbers  
    \- Test recording with pass/fail  
    \- Photo and certification upload  
    \- SWI and risk assessment generation  
    \- Portal access for customers

### Non-Functional Requirements

- \- Security: Data encryption and secure access  
    \- Performance: Fast document generation  
    \- Offline capability for engineers

### Data Model Summary

Entities: Project, Substation, Asset, Results, Document, Customer  
Relationships: One Project → Many Assets → Many Tests → Documents linked to Project

### Document Templates

SWI, Risk Assessment, Asset Spreadsheet

### Integration Points

Mobile App, Backend API, Document Generation Service, Customer Portal

### Business Workflow (Under new system)

The utility infrastructure provider contacts the commissioning agent about the job. The commissioning agent provides a quote and wins the job.  
An **admin** adds a new job into the system through the administrative area of the app. This entry includes the date and time, location, job details, and tags (tags are a quick way to describe the job, such as metering, stop button, required equipment, etc.).  
The admin can then assign the job to one or more staff members. Once assigned, the job will appear on the engineer's list within the app. Within the Admin area a list of test equipment can be managed and added to.

When the engineer arrives at the site, they can select the job on their job list and will have the following options:

- Risk Assessment
- Asset Management
- Commissioning Test
- Image/Scan

_Risk Assessment Fields Required_

Once the job is completed, the engineer can select **"Generate Document."** This action will create the Custom Energy Document version for Risk Assessments, Test Results, and the SWI.  
For utilities such as _Power On_ that require their own document format, there will be an area in the admin panel to upload these templates and map the fields. This setup will allow the engineer to download a Power On-specific version of the document, for example.

<br/>**Image/Scan Section** - When in the job area of the app (after selecting a job from the job list), the top-right corner will display a camera icon. Selecting this icon allows the engineer to take photos of assets and scan certifications. These files will be uploaded against the job and can be individually downloaded later.

**Portal** - The portal is a separate application from the engineer app. While it will remain mobile and tablet friendly, it will be designed primarily for laptop users.  
Commissioning agents' customers (such as _Power On_) will be able to sign up to this system. Once signed up and verified, the portal will display a list of all jobs completed by the commissioning agent.
